<br>
The way the game works is for people to sit on long spawns for ages until they get what they came for.  The TLC will do wonders for alleviating some of the tensions that come with spawn, but you will still see people fussing and fighting over camps.  <br>
<br>
It is and always has been my opinion that people who invoke the PNP every time someone is hunting the critters that *they* would like to hunt are simply troublemakers who are impatient and can't bear to wait a bit for their chance at &quot;what they deserve&quot;.   The PNP has been a miserable failure and always results in hurt feelings.  More often than not it is not evoked to resolve a particular spawn dispute but rather as a means to intimidate and coerce other players into bending to the will of the petitioner.  Far from the scenario laid out by Banegrivm, it is usually the PNP invokers who are the ones looking to suppress and &quot;downtrod&quot; others. When someone uses the PNP on a group I am in, I usually leave.  If I am in a group and someone decides they want to steal a camp from another group by invoking PNP, I disband and go along my way.<br>
<br>
When I come to a camp and it already has someone there, I ask to join. If they say no, I move along. Simple and easy.<br>
<br>
I am beginning to realize that there is very little difference between the people who are most vocal about FV and those who are most vocal about SZ.  Same strategies, same tactics, same attitude. Simply different language.  I just wish people would be nicer to one another and not be so aggressive and hateful.<br>
<br>
On SZ, I was strongly against corpse camping and griefing in general. That view is the exception as most people view it as &quot;the intention of the no rules server&quot;.  Those people tend to get upset when you differ with them on that issue or any other.  Here it is the goosestepping rhetoric of purity that is the chant.  &quot;This is the RP server&quot;.  Again, differeing with those people with the goal of trying to achieve a little bit of mutual respect for each others is shouted down as not &quot;hardcore RP&quot; enough.  Instead of &quot;Go back to your bluebie server poon!&quot;, here it is &quot;Go back to your phat lewtz dOOd!&quot;.  The irony is indeed thick.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubanegrivm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Banegrivm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/3/01 1:05:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=20>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: and yet again I am forced to say, Hrmmm</span><hr size=1> I don't see any irony in people declaring they are going to try and farm the hell out of a server, I find it an outright disgust and an abberation. Quite simple, they do not want to be in a RP environment and plan on abusing the economy, go to another server. Its pretty plain and simple. Common sense.<br>
<br>
I have only used PnP twice. Will I do it again? Anytime I see ANYONE trying to throw their weight around or outright state they will farm. They don't like it? Their are other servers.<br>
<br>
First time I saw an uber in unrest who tried to steal my groups camp from us and started KS'ing us. He was 50 plus, we were hunting there. Why wasn't he in kunark or vellious getting uber gear? He claimed he needed boots for his warrior. I petitioned, he got booted.<br>
<br>
Second time was a lad that tried to start KSing my group at the Loathsome individuals and then he tried to train us. I petitioned, he got forcibly ejected. They want to be abusive, they want to throw their weight around...then they are welcome to meet the brick wall called PnP. It is plain and simple and no one is above it.<br>
<br>
I never hesitate to share and myself and my guild have oft even invited strangers from out of the blue and even other guilds to our camps. We have even handed camps over to those more in need then ourselves. I don't see the problem. We respect others and the system and laws as they may be. I do not respect ANYONE who abuses them or thinks they are above them. <p>Banegrivm Shadowblight<br>Sovereign Lord of the 1st Fist of Light<br>www.1stfistoflight.com</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umorrizarthesorcerer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Morrizar the Sorcerer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/3/01 1:05:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: and yet again I am forced to say, Hrmmm</span><hr size=1> /agree with Bludge<br>
